Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.52,0:00:58.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew I was gone all the time.\NHere
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.39,0:01:02.71,Default,,0,0,0,,we are in Toronto. Wonderful, beautiful\Ncity.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.71,0:01:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't remember ever having been here\Nbefore.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.00,0:01:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, visited Magna Falls, calibrated\Nthe energy of uh Toronto
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.24,0:01:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,at the request.\NAmerica's at 421, Toronto's at 423.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.84,0:01:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,various cities at different levels.\NToronto
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.60,0:01:37.75,Default,,0,0,0,,is a very good city. Beautiful. All\Nright.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.75,0:01:44.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we came today to together to review\Nuh uh the impact of the work and what
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.47,0:01:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,we've learned from it as it applies to\Nhuman consciousness as it applies to
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.60,0:01:56.39,Default,,0,0,0,,everyone in the audience.\NSo we're going to do today is um
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.39,0:02:04.39,Default,,0,0,0,,discover how things come to be and then\Na group like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.39,0:02:08.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The problem is going to be how to\Ntranscend the intellect
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.23,0:02:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the world of duality. And so we're going\Nto trace the evolution of the ego from
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.04,0:02:18.31,Default,,0,0,0,,the beginning of time up to the present\Ntime. And once you understand the nature
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.31,0:02:24.23,Default,,0,0,0,,of the ego,\Nit's much easier to transcend it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.23,0:02:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The traditional way has been to oppose\Nthe ego and declare it as evil and sin.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.48,0:02:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh see it as the downside of life,\Nsomething to be conquered,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.20,0:02:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,something to feel guilty about,\Nfrightened of, angry about.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.92,0:02:45.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, we're going to see how it\Nevolves
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.12,0:02:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and we're going to adopt our ego, love\Nit, and transcend it. Dissolve it,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.48,0:02:58.16,Default,,0,0,0,,which is easier than the sack cloth of\Nashes. Go on your knees from here to the
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.16,0:03:03.68,Default,,0,0,0,,pyramid back again or something.\NOkay. Say, would Jesus have a
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.68,0:03:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,microphone?\NIf everybody asks you would Jesus do
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.36,0:03:20.23,Default,,0,0,0,,this or Jesus do that\Nmake it in this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.23,0:03:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,>> He said me instead.\N>> Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.84,0:03:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So we begin with the ending of the\Nlectures. will begin in the end and then
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.04,0:03:44.95,Default,,0,0,0,,move backwards to the beginning. Saves a\Nlot of time that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.95,0:03:50.23,Default,,0,0,0,,A group like this, the difficulty this\Nis a very areaike group. Uh this group
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.23,0:03:56.87,Default,,0,0,0,,is probably over 423 424.\NYeah, this is a this these groups uh
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.87,0:04:04.23,Default,,0,0,0,,like this are\Nyou know educated and intelligent and
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.23,0:04:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,so the the mind and the ego which is\Nwhat brings us into the awareness the
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.51,0:04:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual truth and gives us the the\Nmotivation to study it uh then becomes
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.32,0:04:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,the limitation. So, it is the canoe and\Nuh at the other side of the creek, how
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.84,0:04:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,do you let go of the canoe?\NHow to transcend the canoe? So, a group
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.36,0:04:32.08,Default,,0,0,0,,like this, we're still dragging our\Ncanoe.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.08,0:04:38.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It got us this far and now how do we get\Nrid of it? So, they were going to figure
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.24,0:04:46.47,Default,,0,0,0,,out how to transcend your canoe and so\Nyou'd be free on the other side.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.47,0:04:52.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The big difficulty with an educated\Ngroup like this is we're stuck in the
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.08,0:04:57.75,Default,,0,0,0,,world of causality. We're stuck in the\NNewtonian paradigm of reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.75,0:05:03.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The ego is dualistic.\NIt believes in a this that causes a
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.19,0:05:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,that.\NThe pathway I teach is called devotional
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.28,0:05:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,nonduality.\NDevotional nonduality. How to transcend
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.56,0:05:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,the v thisness and the thatness, the\Ndualistic
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.24,0:05:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,ego which confuses perception with\Nessence. It thinks that it's the cause
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.28,0:05:30.72,Default,,0,0,0,,of things. Therefore, you're subject to\Nguilt, anxiety, fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.72,0:05:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,If there's a this causing a that, then\Nthere must be a this within here causing
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.60,0:05:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,a that.\NAnd that reinforces the illusion of the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.08,0:05:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,reality of the ego. And therefore, we're\Ngoing to figure out today we'll we'll
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.88,0:05:51.03,Default,,0,0,0,,illustrate clearly how to transcend it.\NSo we'll start at the end of the lecture
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.03,0:05:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,of how things actually come into\Nmanifestation.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.00,0:06:05.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Each and everything\Nbecomes what it is
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.91,0:06:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,as the actualization of a potential,\Nnot as a result of any external cause
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.84,0:06:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,within the invisible domain, the\Nunmanifest.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.75,0:06:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,There be there is the potentiality.\NPotentiality
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.96,0:06:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,within an infinite powerful field\Nbecomes an actuality.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.16,0:06:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Each thing\Nbecomes the expression of that which it
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.88,0:06:40.47,Default,,0,0,0,,is\Nsolely on its own
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.47,0:06:46.63,Default,,0,0,0,,not due to anything else out there.\NThe flower has the potentiality. The
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.63,0:06:54.56,Default,,0,0,0,,seed has potentiality.\NYou put that seed in an infinite a field
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.56,0:07:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,of infinite power.\NIts potentiality becomes an actuality
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.16,0:07:11.91,Default,,0,0,0,,when conditions are appropriate.\NIt only awaits appropriate conditions.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.91,0:07:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You can picture how life comes about\Nthen. The infinite divinity, the
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.12,0:07:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,infinite field of consciousness\Nis the unmanifest which becomes manifest
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.80,0:07:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,knowable experience as infinite field of\Nconsciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.16,0:07:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The infinite field of consciousness is\Nlike a giant electromagnetic like a
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.63,0:07:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,giant electrostatic field.\NElectromagnetic electrostatic field of
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.12,0:07:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,infinite power and infinite dimension\Nwhich includes all that is
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.08,0:07:54.31,Default,,0,0,0,,out of the unmanifest arises the\Nmanifest which first presents
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.31,0:08:00.63,Default,,0,0,0,,as the infinite field of consciousness\Nof infinite power.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.63,0:08:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,to go into states of enlightenment. One\Nof the staggering things is the
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.08,0:08:11.91,Default,,0,0,0,,recognition, the realization\Nof the degree of power. The power is so
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.91,0:08:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,incredible that it's beyond all\Nimagination.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.44,0:08:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Its absoluteness is absolute.\NWhen dealing with the infinite,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.24,0:08:30.80,Default,,0,0,0,,you're dealing with the absolute. The\Nabsolute
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.80,0:08:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The absolute which is also exquisitly\Ngentle.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.56,0:08:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The presence is like\Ninfinite power beyond all comprehension
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.12,0:08:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,at the same time exquisitly soft.\NIt melts what was left of the personal
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.44,0:08:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,self.\NTherefore, things happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.92,0:09:00.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Happen is\Nthe way we observe things. We say they
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.08,0:09:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,happen.\NWhat we mean is we just notice it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.80,0:09:08.95,Default,,0,0,0,,We just notice it because it's a\Ncontinuity. The fact that you notice it
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.95,0:09:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't cause it happening.\NIt's just that you noticed it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.36,0:09:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Each and everything then within a power\Ninfinite an infinite power electro
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.24,0:09:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,magnetic field. Each of us is like a\Nlittle iron filing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.60,0:09:36.39,Default,,0,0,0,,We karmically evolve over vast eons of\Ntime. Today we'll look at how it arises
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.39,0:09:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,vast of time to become that way\Nthroughout we are. So you could picture
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.44,0:09:47.27,Default,,0,0,0,,yourself like a little molecule or a\Nlittle iron filing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.27,0:09:51.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And what you look like depends on all\Nthe decisions
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.51,0:09:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and things you've done throughout an\Ninfinite number of lifetimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.00,0:10:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,As a consequence of this, you look like\Nthis or like this or however. So,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.72,0:10:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,however you're going to be in this giant\Nfield depends on your configuration.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.48,0:10:11.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, nothing is arbitrary. The\Njustice of God is continuous
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.60,0:10:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,absolute ongoing.\NOne doesn't have to worry about judgment
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.56,0:10:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,day being later. Judgment day is right\Nnow. Every moment is judgment day. Every
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.20,0:10:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,moment like an iron fing you are exactly\Nat the perfect place within this giant
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.32,0:10:38.48,Default,,0,0,0,,electromagnetic field.\NConsequently, if you leave the body, if
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.48,0:10:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,you leave the body,\Nworld gets emotional about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.48,0:10:51.51,Default,,0,0,0,,When you leave the body, it's fantastic.\NYou're free of it. Oh, there's a lane
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.51,0:11:00.95,Default,,0,0,0,,down there and you are exactly in the\Nperfect place.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.95,0:11:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Where else could you be except\Nwhere you are and where you are depends
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.56,0:11:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,on what you have become. So all happens\Nautonomously as a consequence of that
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.44,0:11:33.36,Default,,0,0,0,,which it is.\NEverything that comes into
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.36,0:11:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,manifestation,\Nit has a potential potential with a
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.36,0:11:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,within a infinite power in a field of\Ninfinite power then actualizes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.00,0:11:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Potentuality becomes actuality.\NEach thing arises of its own as a
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.36,0:11:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,consequence\Nand with the intrinsic design.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.60,0:12:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,To understand the design, it's useful to\Nlook at Sheldre's
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.64,0:12:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Sheldrake\Ndiscovered
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.56,0:12:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,that what he calls formative causation.\NThe design of things prior to the emerg
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.92,0:12:19.60,Default,,0,0,0,,their emergence within the world.\NThe design occurs in a field of
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.60,0:12:25.83,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness.\NA very powerful and interesting concept.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.83,0:12:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,We can see it in the construction of the\NEmpire State Building.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.39,0:12:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The man sitting at his desk with his\Nfeet up there smoking a cigar and he
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.04,0:12:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,says, "Wow, what if we built the tallest\Nbuilding in the world?"
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.00,0:12:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Tallest building in the world. In his\Nmind, he sees this thing going up like
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.16,0:12:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,that. He gets enthused. He starts to\Ntalk it up. Bank anchors get interested.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.92,0:12:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Union is bid for the job. Won't walk\NIndians are the only ones who could
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.16,0:13:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,climb all the way up there anyway.\NSteel company's bid. You see how the
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.72,0:13:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,whole thing the banks underwrite it. But\Nit was just a vision in his mind. And
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.00,0:13:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,now the whole thing manifests.\NAnd in the middle of the depression,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.88,0:13:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Empire State Building went up in exactly\None year. One year. God's building the
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.63,0:13:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,world of time all came out of nowhere\Nwasn't caused by anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.44,0:13:32.63,Default,,0,0,0,,There isn't any building causer machine\Nthat produced it out of nothingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.63,0:13:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So\Nthe other thing to know is that
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.12,0:13:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,everything arises out of nothing\Nespecially thoughts. As you meditate,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.88,0:13:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,you realize, you see, if you're stuck in\Ncausality, the Newtonian paradigm, you
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.56,0:13:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,think one thought is causing another\Nthought,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.60,0:13:59.76,Default,,0,0,0,,an infinite series of thoughts. And\Npeople are frustrated with meditation
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.76,0:14:04.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and say, "I can't get my thoughts to\Nstop." With close observation, you'll
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.39,0:14:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,see that each thought is rising out of\Nnothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.72,0:14:13.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It arises out of nothing. The next stop\Narises out of nothing. They're not like
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.51,0:14:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,bills sequentially going from A to Z.\NEach one arises independently.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.24,0:14:29.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It could arise A and then B and then C.\NBut they all arose from nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.12,0:14:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The B does not arise from the A. The B\Narises from nothing. The sea arises from
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.36,0:14:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,,nothing. Each thing\Nthoughts emerge like flying fish out of
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.24,0:14:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the sea.\NThe sea is the nothingness, the
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.00,0:14:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,potentiality, capacity, the think\Nconsciousness itself. Here comes a
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.68,0:14:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,flying fish. Here comes another one and\Nanother one. Here comes another one.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.88,0:14:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Flop all over the deck.\NI was into the South Pacific and they
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.44,0:15:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,would fly all over. Now this line, this\Nfish here does not cause this fish here
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.72,0:15:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,to come up. You understand? So the\Nobserver could say, well, the first one
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.63,0:15:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,up is A. This is fish A. This is fish B.\NThis is the seat the seat that came up
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.36,0:15:20.95,Default,,0,0,0,,like ABC but the ABC is in your mind\NABC in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.95,0:15:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So\Nmain
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.44,0:15:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,observation\Nthere is rest kajans
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.32,0:15:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,rest internal that is the world of\Nthinkingness the mind and then there is
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.04,0:15:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,rest external the world as it is nature\Nthe world as it is without ugly thoughts
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.12,0:15:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,about it\Nand it's a griev mistake the two to
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.76,0:15:53.27,Default,,0,0,0,,think that rit intern represents That's\Nfor sex externa. What you think about
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.27,0:15:57.75,Default,,0,0,0,,the world is one thing. What the world\Nis is something else. Very often you're
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.75,0:16:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,not related at all.\NMore often than not,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.44,0:16:09.27,Default,,0,0,0,,you have no relationship at all.\NAppearance is not essence. Occurrence is
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.27,0:16:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,not essence.\NTherefore, one of the classic
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.04,0:16:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual\Ntools has been humility.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.16,0:16:31.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The awareness that the mind alone unaded\Nup in and of itself is unable to discern
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.04,0:16:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,reality.\NThat was the most major stunning
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.07,0:16:41.27,Default,,0,0,0,,discovery of all the work we did. The\Nmind in and of itself by virtue of its
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.27,0:16:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,construction is dualistic construction.\NThe ego by virtue of how it's
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.92,0:16:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,constructed is incapable of telling\Ntruth from falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.44,0:17:04.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So much for pontification.\NI see people on TV their faces red with
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.31,0:17:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,emotion waving their hands and fists and\Nstuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.64,0:17:14.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you calibrate what they're\Ntalking about, it calibrates like 120.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.31,0:17:23.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Completely the opposite of the truth.\NThat doesn't prevent people from
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.03,0:17:28.79,Default,,0,0,0,,believing it. So\Nthroughout time it said that life is
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.79,0:17:34.79,Default,,0,0,0,,impossible without the help of an\Nadvanced spiritual teacher. Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.79,0:17:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Because\Nthe mind in and of itself is unable to
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.36,0:17:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,discern reality. Cannot tell. Therefore,\Nthe great teachers throughout all time
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.20,0:17:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,arose,\Narrived, developed, evolved, popped out
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.00,0:17:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,of\Ninitiality and to act to actuality.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.72,0:18:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Um\Nto make people aware of what is what is
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.84,0:18:07.84,Default,,0,0,0,,truth. You call that truth spiritual.\NThat's sort of labeling me. What if we
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.84,0:18:11.60,Default,,0,0,0,,didn't use the word religion or\Nspiritual? Well, what if we just said
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.60,0:18:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,that's truth?\NAnything wrong with that? It would solve
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.20,0:18:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,all kinds of rivalries, wouldn't it?\NEverybody could give up war because it's
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.16,0:18:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,always based on some\Nphilosophic religious premise.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.60,0:18:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,What if we just said the only thing\Nthat's true about truth is truth and we
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.20,0:18:39.91,Default,,0,0,0,,don't care who said it.\NI don't care who said it. George Peabody
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.91,0:18:45.03,Default,,0,0,0,,not to kiss his butt because he said\Ntruth. I mean what is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.03,0:18:50.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Some guy knew the truth.\NYou know the truth is so rare in the
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.64,0:18:56.08,Default,,0,0,0,,history of mankind that we have called\Nthem avatars.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.08,0:19:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,man in and of himself uninfant know what\Nis the truth and the occasional
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.36,0:19:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,individual who\Nmanifested that then is so rare that we
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.48,0:19:15.12,Default,,0,0,0,,re rever them throughout history\Nman had no way to know truth and false
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.12,0:19:19.84,Default,,0,0,0,,except by the authority of an\Nenlightened being the great avatars
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.84,0:19:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,great saviors of mankind alone knew the\Ntruth
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.48,0:19:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It recurred throughout time. The great\Nsages of ancient India thousands of
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.32,0:19:40.64,Default,,0,0,0,,years before Christ, before Buddha\Nstated the same truth. So we see that
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.64,0:19:45.12,Default,,0,0,0,,the same truth is rediscovered,\Nre-realized,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.12,0:19:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,repronounced,\Nspoken of again over and over throughout
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.67,0:19:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,time, usually with long time lapses. But\Nthe truth is always the same. No matter
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.64,0:20:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,what culture, no matter what era,\Nwhether it was 7,000 BC,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.28,0:20:09.12,Default,,0,0,0,,whether it was the time of the Buddha\N500 BC, whether it was Christ
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.12,0:20:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Zoraster,\Nthe truth has always been the same. Each
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.67,0:20:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,one who's discovered it spontaneously,\Nautonomously
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.24,0:20:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,have declared it to be exactly the same.\NThere's no difference. No difference
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.00,0:20:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,to a group like this which is destined\Nto enlightenment or else they wouldn't
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.52,0:20:38.32,Default,,0,0,0,,be here.\NPeople in this room are distant for
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.32,0:20:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,enlightenment.\N>> People in this room are distant for
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.67,0:20:48.15,Default,,0,0,0,,enlightenment. Otherwise, they wouldn't\Nbe here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.15,0:20:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're into golf, you'd be out on the\Ngolf course.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.15,0:20:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Who would be at a lecture like this\Nunless they people were in you know
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.40,0:21:05.67,Default,,0,0,0,,distant that was their destiny. Okay\Nto make the road easier then we'll try
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.67,0:21:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,to describe how the ego evolved what its\Nnature is and therefore how to transcend
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.55,0:21:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,it because\Nit is perception that stands in the way
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.88,0:21:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,of the realization of truth.\NEach thing then comes into existence by
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.76,0:21:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,virtue of its potentiality becoming an\Nactuality
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.36,0:21:39.03,Default,,0,0,0,,under appropriate conditions.\NThat gets rid of blame.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.03,0:21:45.12,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing out there causing\Nanything to be any other than what it
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.12,0:21:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,is. Nothing's causing it.\NEverything is happening
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.20,0:22:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,is the actualization of its potentiality\Nwithin a field of infinite power.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.55,0:22:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That explanation, let's see,\Nthat explanation calibrates over 800,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.00,0:22:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,850,\N840. It's good enough for today.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.88,0:22:30.72,Default,,0,0,0,,toonian causality calibrates about 460.\NAll right. So what we're describing is
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.72,0:22:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,how it actually comes about a deal\Ncloser to the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.96,0:22:42.08,Default,,0,0,0,,We witness potentiality becoming\Nactuality because the conditions are
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.08,0:22:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,appropriate\Nand it happens because of the infinite
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.03,0:22:56.32,Default,,0,0,0,,power of the field.\NThere was a seed alongside the road in
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.32,0:23:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,uh Arizona\Nthat you started to all of a sudden this
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.36,0:23:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,century plant started to come up.\NThere's nothing there. nothing but dirt.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.40,0:23:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, that seed laid there 150 years.\NWe calibrated it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.84,0:23:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,150 years this seed lay there and\Nsuddenly out of nowhere the conditions
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.67,0:23:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,are appropriate and this incredible\Ncentury plant shoots up and within one
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.24,0:23:27.12,Default,,0,0,0,,seating becomes this glorious and\Nfantastic and magnificent display.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.12,0:23:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Seemingly out of nowhere after waiting\N150 years, 150 years. You say, well, it
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.24,0:23:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,rained a lot of times in 150 years,\Nbut currently not the right combination
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.00,0:23:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,to trigger the whole phenomena.\NTherefore, you can't always tell from
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.84,0:23:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,local conditions what's causal. As you\Nlook around at this plant every year,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.88,0:23:55.91,Default,,0,0,0,,there's no conditions there to\Npotentiate its growth. Why 150 years out
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.91,0:24:00.15,Default,,0,0,0,,of seeming nothingness does this plant\Nsuddenly arise?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.15,0:24:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. So I thought today we'll\Ncover the basics and we'll also describe
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.84,0:24:09.36,Default,,0,0,0,,somewhat how these awarenesses came\Nabout
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.36,0:24:13.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and we'll take a break in the morning\Nand we'll have lunch we'll take another
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.91,0:24:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,break in the afternoon and then we'll\Nhave personal questions and answers. All
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.60,0:24:23.12,Default,,0,0,0,,right. So let's let's see we do have\Nslides. Let's start with the calibrated
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.12,0:24:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,levels of consciousness which are\Nbecoming
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.32,0:24:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,pretty rather widespread within the\Nworld relatively well known. We have a
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.00,0:24:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,pointer here.\NWe had a great one which we I left in my
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.55,0:24:42.64,Default,,0,0,0,,suitcase.\NTherefore, God must want me to have this
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.64,0:24:53.84,Default,,0,0,0,,one. Right.\Nwork.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.84,0:24:57.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, I made this is supposed to\Nhave a flag on it. I saw it off the flag
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.27,0:25:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,thing, took the flag off, and now I have\Na point.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.96,0:25:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Theiology is a strange phenomenon.\Nphysiology
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.76,0:25:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the the abs the only absolute in the\Nuniverse then is an infinite field of
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.52,0:25:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness which is the absolute\Nphilosopher Hegel in the beginning of
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.60,0:25:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,the 1800s\None of his principles was that of the
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.48,0:25:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,absolute\Nabsolute there is an absolute
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.00,0:25:39.67,Default,,0,0,0,,by which all else can be to which all\Nelse can be compared
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.67,0:25:47.27,Default,,0,0,0,,an absolute reality, not an absolute\Nhypothesis, but an absolute existent
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.27,0:25:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,reality by which and against which\Neverything else can be deferred. That
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.40,0:25:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,was never discovered before and it was\Nonly a philosophic proposition even in
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.84,0:26:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the 1800s.\NBut that's exactly what we're relying
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.76,0:26:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,on.\NThe field of consciousness then is like
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.52,0:26:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,a giant electrostatic field. You\Nremember the days of electro
