Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.76,0:26:22.72,Default,,0,0,0,,big jumps and it was so the\Nelectrostatic speaker is really just a
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.72,0:26:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,charged membrane that's it's one charged\Npositive or negative I forget which
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.52,0:26:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't difference\None or the other.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.88,0:26:37.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and you bring up electrons of of an\Nopposite charge. So the electrostatic
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.91,0:26:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,field is really a potential. It doesn't\Ndo anything. It just is. Then when you
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.64,0:26:50.79,Default,,0,0,0,,bring up a certain charge, it\Nautomatically responds
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.79,0:26:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,complete and totally opposite to the\Ncharge but to the exact degree.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.72,0:27:02.32,Default,,0,0,0,,82 billion electrons here result in 82\Nbillion posetrons. So that on opposite
