Dialogue: 0,1:21:54.63,1:21:59.12,Default,,0,0,0,,in age 12, I had the longest paper out\Nin Wisconsin,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:59.12,1:22:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,18 miles every day below zero.\NOne night came below zero lizard pitch
Dialogue: 0,1:22:05.92,1:22:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,black. There was no electricity. We live\Nway on the sticks. Electricity was only
Dialogue: 0,1:22:09.92,1:22:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,on one side of the highway. So in the\Npitch act with no electricity
Dialogue: 0,1:22:15.60,1:22:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,timbal\Nthe wind blew the papers out of the back
Dialogue: 0,1:22:19.28,1:22:24.56,Default,,0,0,0,,of my bicycle and I started to cry with\Nfrustration trying to chase the pickers
Dialogue: 0,1:22:24.56,1:22:30.71,Default,,0,0,0,,across the icy snow\Nand finally gave up. So I dug my way
Dialogue: 0,1:22:30.71,1:22:35.28,Default,,0,0,0,,into a snowbank in Wisconsin. By the end\Nof January the snow was about 12 ft
Dialogue: 0,1:22:35.28,1:22:41.67,Default,,0,0,0,,high. I dug a hole in this through the\Ncrust of the snow, climbed into this
Dialogue: 0,1:22:41.67,1:22:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,little space out of the wind. Main thing\Nwas to get up
Dialogue: 0,1:22:46.00,1:22:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and almost instantly an exquisite\Npresence,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:54.80,1:22:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,which is not really possible to talk\Nabout.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:59.04,1:23:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,There was an ex exquisite presence like\Nthe very essence of love itself which
Dialogue: 0,1:23:04.88,1:23:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,melted away any thinkingness,\Nplace, time.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:10.40,1:23:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It was beyond all time, location\Nand it was forever.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:17.04,1:23:23.12,Default,,0,0,0,,That which I am\Nexisted prior to all universes
Dialogue: 0,1:23:23.12,1:23:31.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and will be and all universes\Nhave gone.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:31.12,1:23:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,That is a fact existed.\NThat is a fact.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:36.56,1:23:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,That which I am existed for all\Nuniverses and will be after all
Dialogue: 0,1:23:41.76,1:23:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,universes have disappeared. Beyond all\Ntime, beyond all place, beyond all
Dialogue: 0,1:23:47.44,1:23:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,conditionality.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:52.40,1:23:56.71,Default,,0,0,0,,In exquisite state.\NI don't know whether breathing continued
Dialogue: 0,1:23:56.71,1:24:02.08,Default,,0,0,0,,or not. It sort of wouldn't be\Ninteresting.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:02.08,1:24:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Every time that sleep occurs,\Nyou don't need to eat, drink, think,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:07.28,1:24:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,feel, nothing.\NAnd whether the body continues or not is
Dialogue: 0,1:24:12.32,1:24:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,irrelevant.\NWhether it does or not depends on karmic
Dialogue: 0,1:24:16.48,1:24:20.71,Default,,0,0,0,,propensities and conditions. If the\Nconditions are favorable, the body
Dialogue: 0,1:24:20.71,1:24:26.63,Default,,0,0,0,,resumes because somebody comes along and\Nfeeds it.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:26.63,1:24:30.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And since you eat\Nit's Thursday, you haven't eaten since
Dialogue: 0,1:24:30.71,1:24:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Tuesday. So, okay.\NAnyway, in that particular state which
Dialogue: 0,1:24:37.19,1:24:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,goes on beyond time, the experience of\Ninfinity is infinite.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:42.71,1:24:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The foreverness of the existence of the\Ninfinite all presence of God is forever.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:49.44,1:24:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway,\Nsomething was shaking my foot with my
Dialogue: 0,1:24:53.52,1:25:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,father and the 29 Model 8 Ford. He\Nfollowed the my tracks. I showed up for
Dialogue: 0,1:25:00.00,1:25:05.19,Default,,0,0,0,,dinner. So, he discovered that the\Nbody's there
Dialogue: 0,1:25:05.19,1:25:11.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and I didn't need to breathe or be with\Nthe body ever again. I looked at my
Dialogue: 0,1:25:11.04,1:25:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,father and I realized he believes in\Ndeath. He thinks death is reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:17.76,1:25:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, if I didn't breathe again, he\Nwould be stuck with a lifetime of guilt.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:22.32,1:25:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,If he'd allowed his son to die in a\Nblizzard,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:28.00,1:25:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,he would have been struck with a\Nlifetime of guilt.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:32.40,1:25:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So, because I love my father, I\Nbecame
Dialogue: 0,1:25:39.84,1:25:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the energy of the body again.\NI'm sick.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:56.88,1:26:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You see because death is not a\Npossibility.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:01.12,1:26:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Death is not a possibility.\NThere's the law of conservation of
Dialogue: 0,1:26:05.92,1:26:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,matter, law of conservation of energy.\NAnd why mankind has never discovered the
Dialogue: 0,1:26:12.96,1:26:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,law of the conservation of life is\Nbeyond me. It's the most stunningly
Dialogue: 0,1:26:16.48,1:26:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,obvious thing there is. Life can change\Nform, but you cannot kill it.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:24.40,1:26:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You cannot kill it.\NIt just goes out of body and comes back
Dialogue: 0,1:26:29.44,1:26:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,in another form. If you hit a moth or a\Nfly, it doesn't even notice it.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:34.48,1:26:40.71,Default,,0,0,0,,>> You know, they don't they don't even\Nnotice it.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:40.71,1:26:45.19,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a fact. Doesn't even notice it.\NGoes red one clock in his ether atheic
Dialogue: 0,1:26:45.19,1:26:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,body rematerializes in another body.\NOh, you're worrying about the fact that
Dialogue: 0,1:26:51.28,1:26:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,it died. It's having a good time. You\Nknow,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:57.60,1:27:02.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I was a strict Buddhist for many years.\NEach like you had to practice, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:02.32,1:27:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,in New York, biggest in the country.\NAnd uh so there would be flies would get
Dialogue: 0,1:27:08.63,1:27:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,in the middle of the room. You know when\Nyou got a fan going down to get in the
Dialogue: 0,1:27:11.12,1:27:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,middle of the room air conditioner. I\Nwait till the patient leaves and behind
Dialogue: 0,1:27:14.96,1:27:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the drapes I had a butterfly net. As\Nsoon as the patient leave I take out the
Dialogue: 0,1:27:18.96,1:27:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,butterfly net capture these flies and\Nput them out the window and put it back
Dialogue: 0,1:27:22.48,1:27:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,behind the drapes to see the next\Npatient.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:26.08,1:27:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Monu flies.\NI believe that I thought you could kill
Dialogue: 0,1:27:32.32,1:27:38.63,Default,,0,0,0,,life. Well can't kill life.\NCan't kill life. Not possible.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:38.63,1:27:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,When you draw a body, you just say there\Nit is laying there and life goes right
Dialogue: 0,1:27:43.76,1:27:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,on.\NSo this life was sort of different in
Dialogue: 0,1:27:48.96,1:27:57.12,Default,,0,0,0,,many ways. Later on, other uh events uh\Nother events I can't remember what they
Dialogue: 0,1:27:57.12,1:27:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,were. I was going to tell you about\Nthem, but I don't remember what they
Dialogue: 0,1:27:58.80,1:28:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,were.\NOther
Dialogue: 0,1:28:03.04,1:28:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,states that the world calls\Nenlightenment would recur spontaneously
Dialogue: 0,1:28:09.04,1:28:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,in one actually prior to one. Oh, I was\Nan atheist also an atheist for 20 years.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:14.96,1:28:21.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh yes, I was very religious as a kid\Nscrupulosity
Dialogue: 0,1:28:21.19,1:28:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,episcopal.\NI was a boy uh
